,Recommended,289090,30913217,Posted: 2 April,all,Informal Informant,"What the game isApmu-Teais both a game about tea and a play on words. In the game, you play as an Amputee, who has to make tea. Its a basic concept, but the game turns this concept into a challange. AS the steam page says, the game is literally surgion simulator like, but to make tea.Pros+Game has decent graphics.Not state of the art, but not ♥♥♥♥♥♥ either+Gameplay is engaging.Until you figure everything out and beat the game.+Difficult, but not too much.It is difficult at first to do anything. Want to grab a cup, all the others get pushed off the table and onto the floor. Although over time it does go away as you learn the controls.+Sound/Music isnt bad.Sure the music can get annoying after a bit but the sounds go with the art style.Cons-Not to much to do.The concept of the game is to make tea, and thats all you do. It gets old after a while.-Annoying controls.The controls take a while to get used to, and by defealt they are annoying and difficult to use.Final OpinionAmpu-Teais a fun game that can occupy a few hours of time. Its a basic puzzle/physics game (in my mind du to difficulty) that is only somewhat worth the price. For the current $5 it costs, I would only reccomend it if you have spare change and dont mind a challange. But ifApmu-Teais on sale, get it. The game is deffinatly something that can liven up your steam library, and as i've said before, can occupy a few hours of time."
