,Not Recommended,289090,14412423,"Posted: 9 February, 2015",all,𝔹𝕌ℝ𝔾𝕐,"AUDIOAnnoyingVISUALNiceDIFFICULTYGlitchyVIBEGoofy AdventureCRAVINGClassicON SALESometimesPROS:Colorful and somewhat humorous. Environment looks nice.CONS:Amputees struggling in rehabilitation may not be the most tasteful punchline a game could be based off of. More importantly however, the game controls awfully. One might say it was meant to be this way, however games like Octodad and Surgeon Simulator control well... Just clunky to the point of humor. Movement in Ampu-Tea however, is sluggish and often unresponsive. Reeling in fingers to grip is so slow that your fingers will push the item out of grasp. Items will also stick to the hand. Physics move the room about even if you're afk. Sometimes you're notified when you fail immediately, sometimes it waits to notify you at the very end.WORTH:This game may stave off boredom for 15 minutes or so, but is not worth full-price by a long-shot. At the time of writing this, it is on sale for 0.74USD, which is fair for a game that honestly doesn't work very well.OVERALL:The nail in the coffin that keeps this from being the average quick n easy achievement game is the ludicrous achievement requesting you open the program 400 times. I wouldn't recommend this.SCORE:3/10Full Review Coming Soon"
