,Recommended,289090,17530922,"Posted: 13 August, 2015",all,Macheti,"Interesting ""game"". Sure, it looks a lot like Surgeon Simulator (and is completely aware of this, shown by a message on one of the mugs), but it has it's own humorous theme to it. The game is not very serious at all, and is filled with jokes about how British people like drinking tea, and well, that's about it. The controls can be frustrating at times, as some objects refused to be picked up, but other than that, I had an enjoyable hour or two exploring the game, getting the simple and easy achievements, and making a cup of tea with my finicky robotic arm (after maybe 30 retries). If you play around with all the features you will have at least some fun, unless you are a person that gets bored/frustrated easily. I recommend getting it on a sale, as I did.7/10"
