,Recommended,289090,21357975,"Posted: 20 February, 2016",all,Redbeard,"Ampu-Tea is a game for robot nerds, or tea nerds, or maybe just for nerds in general.This is a game for people with some patience. If you want an exciting shoot-'em-up gaming experience, then Ampu-Tea is not for you - walk away now! That's right, get out of here, non-nerd, and don't come back!Now that the neanderthal troglodytes have gone, let's get back to the review.The aim of the game is to make a nice mug of tea, using a robotic arm.There are a number of different instructions given to you, in order to make several mugs of tea.However, the basic tasks are to get a mug off a shelf and then add a tea bag, some sugar, and boiling water - and then serve on a tray (there are several variations of these tasks).To start the game, push ""F1"" for English (assuming that is the language you want, of course) - I mention that because I have had the start screen come up looking blurred once, and couldn't read the instruction in the top left corner to press F1.Press ""H"" to show or hide the help screen - very useful for learning the controls.Don't be surprised if you knock the entire shelf of mugs off the table - I was knocking everything over before I got used to how the robotic arm worked.Try to manoeuvre the mug into place in front of the tea-maker, before adding any tea or sugar, as it is easier to do everything with the mug already in place.Picking up the sugar cubes can be a real pain. Be prepared to drop them many times.Hint: Put the tray in its place first (in front of the tea-maker), so you can serve the tea on it later (otherwise you can make your mug of tea and then spill it when trying to put it onto a tray).The controls can take a bit of getting used to, but then it's much easier after that.A good experience for children who might have a talent for robotics.This game is for nerds only - it is recommended on that basis."
